themes: Funding equity for emerging and lesser-known artists
Overconcentration of support for already successful bands
Need for more diverse artistic voices
Insufficient venues and support for non-mainstream arts
Activation and utilization of existing cultural spaces
key_phrases: Mostly with money & make sure it doesn't JUST go to the most successful bands and no one else
Emerging or lesser known work HAS to be supported
If a band already has an audience, let them cook with that
We need more voices, all the time
We need a lot more venues for plays, painters, filmmaking, writing, and other less rah-rah exciting rock 'n' roll type arts in this town
ESPECIALLY in the Zilker Hillside Theater and Zach Scott and other already existing programs that should be active---OVERactive---every day of the year
barriers_identified: Funding disproportionately directed to most successful bands
Lack of support for emerging or lesser-known artists
solutions_proposed: Distribute funding beyond the most successful bands
Prioritize support for emerging and lesser-known work
Increase the number and activity of venues for diverse art forms
Ensure existing programs and venues are active every day of the year
